<dl id="n40062e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40062e">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40062e"> 62(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> penitents</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[I]</font>n difficult cases the guardians of the peace were assisted by a body of private detectives, women as well as men: these were called Taww&aacute;b&uacute;n = the Penitents, because like our Bow-street runners, they had given up an even less respectable calling. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 176</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
